narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would recommend that students take Elementary Portuguese if they would like to learn a fascinating romance language with a very enthusiastic professor.
If you already speak Spanish or French, Portuguese is not that hard of a transition and a beautiful/important language to acquire!
This is a fun class, an you learn a good amount for an L1 course. Homework is sparse and not difficult, and you get to drop the lowest test. Definitely take it if oyu want to learn portuguese
Marta is the best teacher on the planet. You will learn portuguese and not even know how it happened. I highly recommend this class--truly outstanding.
I would recommend any language. Portuguese is the 5th most spoken language in the world and I believe it is important to learn a least one language beyond a native language.
Yes-it's a great culture, language and department!
